@@TJvColorButton
<TITLEIMG TJvColorButton>
JVCLInfo
  GROUP=JVCL.Buttons.Push
  FLAG=Component
Summary
  A button that can display a color and a drop-down form to select another color.
Description
  Use TJvColorButton when you need a button to select a color. The TJvColorButton is visually similar
  to the color selection button used in the Display Properties dialog in Windows. To select a color,
  click the button and a color selection form is displayed with the common Windows colors.
  Click one of the color squares to select that color. To select a color not in the form, click the
  "Other" button to display a common color selection dialog.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvColorButton.Color
Summary
  Specifies the currently selected color in the button.
Description
  Use Color to specify the color to display on the button. \Read Color to determine what color is
  currently selected. You can't change the color of the actual button as this is determined by the
  clBtnFace color constant.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvColorButton.CustomColors
Summary
  List of custom colors.
Description
  Use CustomColors to set the custom colors to add to the common color dialog displayed when the
  "Other" button is clicked. \Read CustomColors to determine the custom colors added by the user from
  this dialog.
  CustomColors is assignment compatible with the <LINK TColorDialog.CustomColors, CustomColors>
  property of
  TColorDialog.
See Also
  TColorDialog

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvColorButton.EdgeWidth
Summary
  Specifies the width of the edge surrounding the color square on the button.
Description
  Use EdgeWidth to set the size of the color square on the button. \Read EdgeWidth to determine the
  current size of the color square. EdgeWidth is expressed in pixels.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvColorButton.OnChange
Summary
  Occurs when the color in the color square changes.
Description
  Write a handler for the OnChange event to take specific actions when the Color property is changed.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvColorButton.Options
Summary
  Specifies options for the common color dialog.
Description
  Use Options to specify what options should be enabled when the common color dialog is displayed.
  Options is equivalent to TColorDialog.Options. The common color dialog is displayed when the user
  clicks the "Other" button.
See Also
  TColorDialog.Options

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvColorButton.OtherCaption
Summary
  Specifies the caption of the "Other" button.
Description
  Use OtherCaption to set the text that is displayed on the "Other" button. The "Other" button is
  used to display a common color dialog and is located on the drop-down form of the button.

